text: Denison is an unincorporated community in Spokane County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Denison was established in 1908, and remained in operation until 1967. The community was named after the maiden name of an early settler's wife. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Spokane County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Denison, Washington
